Vice President Mike Pence met with EU High Representative and Vice President Federica Mogherini at the United Nations Headquarters in New York. They discussed increasing pressure on North Korea to stop its aggressive actions and ending Iran's destabilizing activities. They also highlighted the importance of supporting the Euro-Atlantic aspirations of the Western Balkans countries and agreed to work together to promote a peaceful and prosperous European future for the region. Pence thanked Mogherini for the European Union's partnership in addressing shared challenges, and they expressed their anticipation for future cooperation.